            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              The first peak in the graph of <m>x(t) = A \cos (\omega_{0} t - \phi)</m> occurs at 
              <m>\displaystyle t^{*} = \frac{\phi}{\omega_{0}}</m> (called the <term>time lag</term>.
              Determine the time lag for the solution to this problem and sketch a graph of the motion 
