        </ol>
      </p>
   

  <p>
    With <term>damping</term> (<m>c>0</m>), in equation <xref ref="dashpoteqn" text="global" />, we 
    investigate the characteristic roots of <m>mr^{2} + cr + k = 0</m>.
    These are
    <me>
      r = \frac{-c \pm \sqrt{c^{2} - 4mk}}{2m}.
    </me>
    We have three cases:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        <term>Overdamped.</term> <m>c^{2} > 4mk \implies</m> two distinct real roots.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        <term>Critically damped.</term> <m>c^{2} = 4mk \implies</m> one repeated real root.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        <term>Underdamped.</term> <m>c^{2} &#x3C; 4mk \implies</m> two complex conjugate roots.
